	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A lot of games store the blocks closest to the player in a 2D array, where some values are solid and others aren't. You'd fetch the array elements corresponding to the grid cells next to the player, find whether they're solid, and then push the player away from solid elements.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


